  "prompt": "How do I get Jimmy Wales to answer my question on Quora?",
  "response": "Getting Jimmy Wales to answer your question on Quora can be challenging, as he is a high-profile individual and likely receives many requests. However, you can increase your chances by following these steps:\n\n1. **Ask a Thoughtful Question**: Make sure your question is well-phrased, clear, and interesting. Avoid questions that are too broad or can be easily answered by a quick search.\n\n2. **Research**: Look at the kinds of questions Jimmy Wales has answered in the past to get a sense of what he might be interested in. Tailor your question to align with those topics.\n\n3. **Tag Appropriately**: Use relevant tags that Jimmy Wales might be following. Tags related to Wikipedia, internet culture, and entrepreneurship might be good choices.\n\n4. **Follow Him**: Follow Jimmy Wales on Quora. Sometimes, people are more likely to notice and respond to questions from their followers.\n\n5. **Engage with His Content**: Comment on his answers, upvote them, and engage in meaningful ways. Building a rapport might increase the likelihood of him noticing your question.\n\n6. **Promote Your Question**: Share your question with your followers and ask them to upvote it. The more traction your question gets, the more likely it is to be seen by Jimmy Wales.\n\n7. **Direct Request**: If appropriate, you can try politely requesting an answer from him directly in the comments section of a question he has answered before.\n\nRemember, there is no guaranteed method to get a specific person to answer your question, but following these tips can increase your chances.",
